      • testUpcomingWebinarListedCorrectly

        public void testUpcomingWebinarListedCorrectly(boolean rememberMe,
                                               java.lang.String webinarName,
                                               java.lang.String webinarDesc,
                                               java.lang.String webinarStart,
                                               java.lang.String webinarEnd,
                                               int webinarDaysInFuture,
                                               java.lang.String webinarTimezone,
                                               java.lang.String webinarLanguage)
                                        throws java.io.IOException
        Verify upcoming webinar is listed correctly.
        That is, the webinar appears in the upcoming webinars list and is scheduled for the right date and time.
        Parameters:
        rememberMe - the 'Remember me' checkbox is checked, if set to true ... else, it remains unchecked
        webinarName - the webinar name
        webinarDesc - the webinar description (optional information that is user supplied)
        webinarStart - the webinar start date (12 hour format, with AM or PM)
        webinarEnd - the webinar end date (12 hour format, with AM or PM)
        webinarDaysInFuture - the days in future in which the webinar is scheduled
        webinarTimezone - the webinar's timezone
        webinarLanguage - the webinar's language (such as Deutch, English, etc)
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Exception thrown if config.properties (defining login credentials) is not in classpath
